+### Redaction Metadata
+
+Events include a top-level `redactionMetadata` object that describes what was
+redacted without storing the original sensitive value. Producers must update
+this metadata as redaction runs, and CLI/API read paths return only these
+metadata fields:
+
+```json
+{
+  "policyVersion": "lux.redaction.v1",
+  "applied": true,
+  "redactedCount": 2,
+  "redactedFields": ["message", "payload.attributes.<sensitive-key>"],
+  "redactionClasses": ["credential", "authorization-header"]
+}
+```
+
+Required redaction metadata fields:
+
+- `policyVersion`: redaction policy identifier used by the producer.
+- `applied`: true when any content was redacted or truncated.
+- `redactedCount`: number of redaction operations applied.
+- `redactedFields`: event field paths that were redacted. Dynamic sensitive
+  metadata and payload attribute names use `<sensitive-key>` instead of the raw
+  key name.
+- `redactionClasses`: coarse classes such as `credential`,
+  `authorization-header`, `private-key`, `project-path`, `gameplay-sensitive`,
+  or `oversize-text`.
+
